creator: Horace Kephart
description:
LibriVox recording of The book of camping and woodcraft : a guidebook for those who travel in the wilderness by Horace Kephart.
Read in English by James K. White; Nathan Heck; Richard Shipp; Michele Fry; Availle; John Lieder; E Snow; April Walters; Larry Wilson; Gail Timmerman Vaughan; TimoleonWash; Joseph Tabler; MaryAnn
Published in 1906, this Guidebook has become one of the most read and loved outdoor books. The author explains: "MY one aim in writing this little book is to make it of practical service to those who seek rest or sport in the wilderness, or whose business calls them thither." - Summary by Gail Timmerman-Vaughan
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
